./dev/plans/runs/12-TX-ts-python-parity-20260517T204414Z.log:644:{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012yqu6A22mPnA5LapZ7xH4A","type":"tool_result","content":"924\t### TypeScript SDK Python-parity (12-TX)\n925\t\n926\tPer `project_typescript_sdk` memory, TS milestone 1 shipped\n927\t2026-04-07 with the basic five-verb surface but is not yet\n928\tPython-parity. Specific gaps to close in 12-TX (enumerate fully\n929\tat slice-start; preliminary list):\n930\t\n931\t- Instrumentation methods: `engine.counters` / `set_profiling` /\n932\t  `set_slow_threshold_ms` / host-logger subscriber attach — verify\n933\t  TS surface mirrors Python at full fidelity.\n934\t- Typed exception hierarchy: TS must expose the same 15-class\n935\t  hierarchy Python does (EngineError + 14 leaf types).\n936\t- Admin verb: `admin.configure` — confirm TS shape matches Python.\n937\t- Type-stub completeness: TS `.d.ts` matches `_fathomdb.pyi`.\n938\t- Test coverage: every Python test under `src/python/tests/` has a\n939\t  TS counterpart under `src/ts/tests/`.\n940\t\n941\tHard reason TS-parity belongs in Phase 12 (not deferred to 0.7.x\n942\talongside logical-id):\n943\t\n944\t- Phase 11 deliberately sliced bindings to ship the SDK surface, but\n945\t  TS shipped at \"milestone 1\" not \"Python-parity\" — leaving TS\n946\t  second-class at GA would be a marketing + adoption hazard.\n947\t- TS substrate (napi-rs binding crate `fathomdb-napi`, npm package\n948\t  config flipped publishable) is already in place from 11b + 11d;\n949\t  remaining work is JS-side wrapper code + tests.\n950\t- Per § \"Slice ordering rationale\", 12-TX runs after 12-P +\n951\t  12-V-VERBS so it doesn't chase a moving runtime surface.\n952\t\n953\t### Deferred items disclosure (must appear in 12-GA release notes)\n954\t\n955\tCarry these forward into the `v0.6.0` release notes verbatim. Each is\n956\tHITL-acknowledged before tagging:\n957\t\n958\t1. **AC-012 / AC-013 / AC-019 perf gates DEFERRED.** Measurement +\n959\t   fixture gaps (dev runner + vec0 bulk-seed). Closeable in\n960\t   0.6.x with canonical-runner re-measurement; no core engine\n961\t   change required.\n962\t2. **AC-020 perf gate DEFERRED.** Architectural gap. Closure requires\n963\t   vendor-SQLite / PCACHE2 / WAL2 / reader-writer-split work\n964\t   (Pack 7). Documented architectural limit at GA.\n965\t3. **Logical-id verbs (`purge_logical_id` + `restore_logical_id`)\n966\t   DEFERRED to 0.7.x.** Canonical-identity substrate is design-only\n967\t   in 0.6.0 per `dev/plans/runs/10b-B-purge-restore-output.json`.\n968\t   Bulk-delete + restore-from-log workflows require 0.7.x.\n969\t4. **TypeScript SDK closes to Python-parity at 12-TX before GA.**\n970\t   Not deferred post-GA — closes in Phase 12 ordering after\n971\t   perf + verb decisions but before docs + tag.\n972\t5. **No 0.5.x compatibility shims or data migrations.** Per\n973\t   `feedback_no_data_migration` + `feedback_reliability_principles`"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e03e003f-16a4-48ce-9857-522e8e7e136e","uuid":"e77d22e7-caa9-4e60-925d-1075260e318c","timestamp":"2026-05-17T20:45:55.787Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/tmp/fdb-12-TX-ts-python-parity-20260517T204414Z/dev/plans/0.6.0-implementation.md","content":"### TypeScript SDK Python-parity (12-TX)\n\nPer `project_typescript_sdk` memory, TS milestone 1 shipped\n2026-04-07 with the basic five-verb surface but is not yet\nPython-parity. Specific gaps to close in 12-TX (enumerate fully\nat slice-start; preliminary list):\n\n- Instrumentation methods: `engine.counters` / `set_profiling` /\n  `set_slow_threshold_ms` / host-logger subscriber attach — verify\n  TS surface mirrors Python at full fidelity.\n- Typed exception hierarchy: TS must expose the same 15-class\n  hierarchy Python does (EngineError + 14 leaf types).\n- Admin verb: `admin.configure` — confirm TS shape matches Python.\n- Type-stub completeness: TS `.d.ts` matches `_fathomdb.pyi`.\n- Test coverage: every Python test under `src/python/tests/` has a\n  TS counterpart under `src/ts/tests/`.\n\nHard reason TS-parity belongs in Phase 12 (not deferred to 0.7.x\nalongside logical-id):\n\n- Phase 11 deliberately sliced bindings to ship the SDK surface, but\n  TS shipped at \"milestone 1\" not \"Python-parity\" — leaving TS\n  second-class at GA would be a marketing + adoption hazard.\n- TS substrate (napi-rs binding crate `fathomdb-napi`, npm package\n  config flipped publishable) is already in place from 11b + 11d;\n  remaining work is JS-side wrapper code + tests.\n- Per § \"Slice ordering rationale\", 12-TX runs after 12-P +\n  12-V-VERBS so it doesn't chase a moving runtime surface.\n\n### Deferred items disclosure (must appear in 12-GA release notes)\n\nCarry these forward into the `v0.6.0` release notes verbatim. Each is\nHITL-acknowledged before tagging:\n\n1. **AC-012 / AC-013 / AC-019 perf gates DEFERRED.** Measurement +\n   fixture gaps (dev runner + vec0 bulk-seed). Closeable in\n   0.6.x with canonical-runner re-measurement; no core engine\n   change required.\n2. **AC-020 perf gate DEFERRED.** Architectural gap. Closure requires\n   vendor-SQLite / PCACHE2 / WAL2 / reader-writer-split work\n   (Pack 7). Documented architectural limit at GA.\n3. **Logical-id verbs (`purge_logical_id` + `restore_logical_id`)\n   DEFERRED to 0.7.x.** Canonical-identity substrate is design-only\n   in 0.6.0 per `dev/plans/runs/10b-B-purge-restore-output.json`.\n   Bulk-delete + restore-from-log workflows require 0.7.x.\n4. **TypeScript SDK closes to Python-parity at 12-TX before GA.**\n   Not deferred post-GA — closes in Phase 12 ordering after\n   perf + verb decisions but before docs + tag.\n5. **No 0.5.x compatibility shims or data migrations.** Per\n   `feedback_no_data_migration` + `feedback_reliability_principles`","numLines":50,"startLine":924,"totalLines":1034}}}
